liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry analysis
Illumina Infinium MethylationEPIC v2.0 BeadChip

definition.value: An Illumina methylation BeadChip that targets  935,000 methylation sites per sample at single-nucleotide resolution.

label.value: multidimensional fatigue inventory score

definition.value: A clinical data item that quantifies the severity of a person's fatigue as measured by a 20-item self-report instrument.

label.value: albumin-free serum

definition.value: A blood serum specimen that contains no albumin.

label.value: fasting

definition.value: A planned process in which an organism drinks only water and does not eat for a specified period of time.

label.value: overnight fasting

definition.value: A fasting with a duration of 8–12 hours, typically occurring overnight.

label.value: fasted

definition.value: An organismal quality that inheres in an organism that has completed a fasting process, and which ceases to inhere in that organism once that organism drinks a liquid other than water or eats.

label.value: water filtration

definition.value: A filtration process of water intended to remove or reduce the concentration of particulate matter, such as suspended particles, parasites, bacteria, algae, viruses, and fungi, as well as other undesirable chemical and biological contaminants.

label.value: minimum resolved unit of measurement

definition.value: An information content entity that indicates the smallest increment that can be resolved on the scale of a measurement instrument.

label.value: ring trial design

definition.value: A study design with the objective of establishing the reproducibility of an experimental approach by performing experiments in different laboratories under the same conditions and comparing the experimental outcomes.

label.value: in vitro CRISPR screen assay

definition.value: An assay in which cells expressing a Cas system are infected with a library of guide RNAs with the intent of causing a perturbation at the target of the guide RNAs.

label.value: in vitro CRISPR screen using single-cell RNA-seq

definition.value: An in vitro CRISPR screen assay that uses single-cell RNA-Seq to detect induced changes in gene expression.

label.value: in vitro CRISPR screen using flow cytometry

definition.value: An in vitro CRISPR screen assay that uses flow cytometry to detect induced changes in gene expression of the targeted genes.

label.value: single-nucleus methylcytosine and transcriptome sequencing assay

definition.value: A DNA methylation profiling by high throughput sequencing assay that measures the cytosine DNA methylation and gene expression signature of single nuclei.

label.value: Illumina NovaSeq X

definition.value: A DNA sequencer with three flow cell types manufactured by Illumina. The NovaSeq X provides an output of up to 8 Tb (26-52 billion reads per run). The sequencer utilizes XLEAP-SBS chemistry, an advanced version of Illumina's sequencing by synthesis (SBS) technology, which enables faster and more accurate sequencing.

label.value: Illumina NovaSeq X Plus

definition.value: A DNA sequencer with three flow cell types manufactured by Illumina. It features a dual-flow cell configuration, allowing to reach an output of up to 16 Tb (52-104 billion reads per run). The sequencer utilizes XLEAP-SBS chemistry, an advanced version of Illumina's sequencing by synthesis (SBS) technology, which enables faster and more accurate sequencing.

label.value: lavage fluid specimen

definition.value: A specimen obtained through a lavage process which includes fluid in addition to cells and/or cellular secretions.

label.value: oral lavage fluid

definition.value: A specimen collected through oral cavity lavage that contains the reagents used to for the lavage process, organisms, cells, cellular secretions, and other biomaterials present in the oral cavity space.

label.value: injection function

definition.value: The function of a device realized when administering a substance in vivo, applied particularly to the forcible insertion of a liquid or gas by means of a syringe, pump, etc.

label.value: Epstein Barr virus transformed B cell

definition.value: A material entity which results from viral transformation process using EBV as transformation agent when applied to B-cell entity

label.value: chimera

definition.value: An organism which contains cells or tissues with a different genotype

label.value: obsolete_anatomical entity

definition.value: An anatomical entity is a material entity that is part of a multicellular organism, and which is large enough so that it forms an identifiable structure in the organism. Specifically, it excludes granular parts of the organism, such as atoms, molecules, cells, which can be removed from the organism without affecting it. It is defined as the union of 'multi-tissue structure', 'body substance' and 'portion of tissue'

label.value: blood plasma specimen

definition.value: a material entity which corresponds to the liquid component of blood, in which the blood cells are suspended.

label.value: blood serum specimen

definition.value: A material entity which derives from blood and corresponds to blood plasma without fibrinogen or the other clotting factors.

label.value: organism

definition.value: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

label.value: obsolete_immortal cell

definition.value: a cell derived from a multicellular organism that has the potential to replicate indefinitely

label.value: obsolete_fragment derived from protein

definition.value: A material entity which is derived from a  protein
